      Because even a Fortune 500 software engineering company would need hundreds of thousands of dollars, perhaps millions (depends on the scope), to develop the project correctly. In addition, some money must be spent to maintain the computational resources necessary (servers, bandwidth, upkeep). That's less of a worry, because that's relatively very cheap compared to the development.<br/><br/>While open source development is an option, I think the quality of the product tends to lag behind products from paid development.<br/><br/>Hope that helps =)

                  
